Overview
We Are Passionate About Supporting the Success of Advisors
At BNY Mellon's Lockwood, we support the success of advisors and their investors. Since 1996, we have helped advisors meet their clients’ ever-changing financial needs. Major world events, regulatory shifts, technology innovations and countless other factors can impact markets in moments. We believe that working with Lockwood can help advisors in successfully managing this complex environment.
Lockwood’s suite of managed account offerings includes comprehensive investment strategies and independent research. We also offer practice management tools, business development support and advisory consulting services to help advisors with their clients’ most unique investment situations. This suite of services is designed to allow advisors to implement thoughtful, disciplined solutions that meet a wide range of client financial needs.






Why BNY Mellon's Lockwood?

We keep the needs of investors at the heart of what we do
We are a long-standing industry leader, providing diverse managed account solutions, portfolio management and research solutions
We take a holistic, long term approach to portfolio construction and risk management for the investors we serve
We provide advisory solutions for investors exclusively through financial organizations and financial advisors, working with the financial intermediaries we serve every day
We have access to the expertise and worldwide resources of The Bank of New York Mellon Corporation including the BNY Mellon Manager Research Group and the BNY Mellon Investment Strategies & Solutions Group
We can provide capital markets commentary and thought leadership to help grow advisors’ businesses and help them navigate the challenging investment arena in part based in our alignment with BNY Mellon and Pershing





Why Lockwood?Watch Video


Investment InsightsRead Commentary








Investment Approach
Philosophy Lockwood’s investment decisions are based on objective research in an effort to eliminate bias toward particular investments or money managers. With access to resources and insights of BNY Mellon, one of the world’s largest investment organizations, Lockwood seeks to deliver superior long-term investment outcomes for clients by emphasizing risk management in our management of portfolios and thorough investment manager selection.
Key philosophy differentiators:

Emphasizing a long-term investment horizon—an approach that seeks to counteract emotional behaviors that can lead to poor investment outcomes
Focus on downside risk management—our experience shows us that steady, long-term wealth accumulation is best achieved by focusing on loss avoidance instead of upside return chasing
A relationship with BNY Mellon—accessing capital market, asset allocation and manager research from one of the world’s largest financial institutions provides our clients with access to best-practice insights similar to those delivered to the largest institutional investors

Portfolio Construction From analyzing asset classes to choosing managers, we believe that our advantage in portfolio construction lies in understanding manager due diligence, research and their connection to the capital markets. Lockwood’s Investment Committee considers in-depth analysis of these factors when making asset allocation and investment research decisions.
Due Diligence by the BNY Mellon Manager Research Group Lockwood works with the BNY Mellon Manager Research Group to conduct initial due diligence and ongoing monitoring of investment managers and vehicles, including:

Qualitative and quantitative investment manager screening and selection
Investment manager monitoring and oversight
Performance analysis and attribution



What We Offer
In today’s world of heightened regulatory scrutiny in the industry and more complex investment strategies, advisors often outsource portfolio management responsibilities or components of the portfolio construction process. Lockwood’s broad range of solutions enables advisors to outsource parts of the investment process, resulting in more time to spend with clients and prospects.
Solutions from BNY Mellon's Lockwood range from separately managed accounts, fixed and flexible mutual fund/ETF wrap offerings and our unified managed account offering where client assets are managed by Lockwood on a fully discretionary basis.
Lockwood’s products and services include:

 Investment management, research and overlay services, giving you access to discretionary services including separately managed accounts, flexible/fixed mutual fund/exchange-traded fund wrap accounts, fixed/flexible unified managed accounts
Investment manager monitoring and oversight
 Business development/field support
 Advisory consulting services

Lockwood’s discretionary investment advisory solutions include:


The Lockwood/American Funds Core Portfolios  The Lockwood/American Funds Core Portfolios combine actively managed American Funds and select, passively managed exchange-traded funds (ETFs) to create an active/passive hybrid portfolio that seeks to provide an efficient and effective investment solution for investors. With a minimum investment of $10,000, these portfolios are attentive to fees, with the goal of enabling investors to meet their long-term investment needs.
Built on the tenets of objectives-based investing, the three unique, diversified portfolios align with key stages of the investor lifecycle:

An appreciation model for the accumulation stage
A balanced model for the transition stage
A conservative growth model for the retirement stage

Lockwood is solely responsible for the fund selection and construction of the portfolios and neither American Funds Distributors, Inc. nor its affiliates are involved in such activities.


Lockwood WealthStart™ PortfoliosLockwood's WealthStart Portfolios (WealthStart) is a mutual fund and/or exchange-traded fund (ETF) account product that is intended to assist emerging and mass affluent investors grow their wealth. They are designed to help advisors reach an often underserved market that may represent tomorrow’s high-net-worth individuals. Lockwood, serving as the portfolio manager, allocates investor assets systematically across multiple asset classes and styles using mutual funds and/or ETFs in the framework of a managed account.
WealthStart is designed to help advisors:

Increase your opportunity to offer a professionally managed investment solution to a broader group of investors
Deliver a cross-generational strategy by providing investment advice to family members from established households who are building their wealth
Transition to an advisory-based practice and evolve your investment offering as the regulatory landscape changes, such as the Department of Labor fiduciary rule
Stay current with Lockwood's thought leadership



Lockwood AdvisorFlex Portfolios™ Lockwood Advisors, Inc.'s, AdvisorFlex Portfolios (AdvisorFlex) offers a series of objectives-based strategies that provide investors with access to professionally managed solutions. These strategies seek to address the unique challenges presented at each phase of the investor lifecycle, from wealth accumulation, to retirement and, ultimately, the management and distribution of income.
There are three distinct objectives-based strategies available in AdvisorFlex, which include the Appreciation Strategy, the Preservation Strategy and the Income Strategy. The AdvisorFlex framework allows advisors to choose from 16 underlying portfolios across the three strategies, created by Lockwood, or customize their client's portfolio by selecting from a variety of investments, including mutual funds, exchange-traded funds (ETFs) in multiple asset classes. Each strategy is designed to meet its intended objective while providing choice and flexibility for the unique needs of individual investors.


Lockwood Asset Allocation Portfolios (LAAP) Lockwood Asset Allocation Portfolios (LAAP) is a discretionary mutual fund/ETF wrap account solution that offers a series of multiple-style portfolios—each held in a single account—and affords the features of diversification and professional management to smaller accounts.
There are five core models ranging from safety of principal to growth. Client portfolios may include open-end mutual funds, ETFs, ETNs and closed-end funds.


Lockwood Investment Strategies (LIS) Lockwood Investment Strategies (LIS) is a discretionary, multi-discipline managed account product housed in a single portfolio. Lockwood, serving as the portfolio manager, determines asset allocation strategy and selects investment vehicles and/or subadvisors for each investment style component of the portfolios based on proprietary modeling strategies.
There are five core models ranging from safety of principal to growth, and portfolios are managed with regard to the investor's tax status and tax efficiency. At the client's discretion, portfolios may include exposure to non-traditional asset classes designed to reduce overall portfolio volatility. Overlay management protocols are used to coordinate the buying and selling of securities, tax efficiency and rebalancing across the entire portfolio. LIS portfolios may include open-end mutual funds, ETFs, ETNs, closed-end funds, alternative investments and individual securities.


Lockwood Separately Managed Accounts—Research Coverage A turnkey SMA solution designed to provide simple and convenient access to money managers under research coverage, which offers access to approximately 60 money managers and more than 90 investment strategies. The covered money managers must undergo an extensive screening process and are subject to ongoing research review.
Lockwood's Separately Managed Account offering includes tools and services to help advisors better serve investors, including extensive web-based account tracking and maintenance tools, consolidated quarterly and on-demand performance reporting, and fee billing and payment services.
Lockwood provides in-depth information about each manager available in Lockwood Separately Managed Accounts—Research Coverage program, including the manager's investment process, availability and fees, as well as news on additions, deletions and changes to the Research Coverage list.


Separately Managed Accounts—Open Architecture This SMA solution is designed to provide your firm with options for building investor portfolios and increased flexibility to add new money managers.* Approximately 150 money managers are available, representing more than 500 investment strategies.
This solution also includes extensive web-based account tracking and maintenance tools, consolidated quarterly and on-demand performance reporting, and fee billing and payment services.* Lockwood reserves the right to accept or reject any proposed money manager.


All of Lockwood’s solutions offer tools and services to help you better serve your clients including extensive Web-based account tracking and maintenance tools, consolidated quarterly and on-demand performance reporting, and fee billing and payment services. The offering streamlines the administrative aspects of transitioning managed account business, allowing you to build and strengthen client relationships.


Management Team


John Brett Chairman and President Lockwood Advisors, Inc., a BNY Mellon Company Managing Director Pershing LLC, a BNY Mellon company
John Brett is a Managing Director and member of the Executive Committee for Pershing LLC, a BNY Mellon company. John is Head of Managed Investments globally, President and Chairman of Lockwood Advisors, Inc. and has senior leadership responsibility for Albridge, an affiliate of Pershing.
John brings over 30 years of experience in the financial services industry to Pershing. Prior to joining the firm in 2013, he was senior vice president and chairman of the MetLife Broker-Dealer Group. In this role, John had responsibility for the investment professionals and investment product management for the broker-dealers within MetLife, including MetLife Securities, MetLife Resources, New England Securities, Tower Square Securities and Walnut Street Securities.
Prior to MetLife, John was a managing director at Black Rock and a director at Lord Abbett. He began his career as an investment professional at Merrill Lynch, and held a number of key distribution roles during his 23 years there.
John earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in Business Administration from Lewis University and is Vice Chairman of the Lewis University Board of Trustees.


Joel Hempel Chief Operating Officer Lockwood Advisors, Inc., a BNY Mellon Company Director Pershing LLC, a BNY Mellon company
Joel Hempel is Chief Operating Officer for Lockwood Advisors, Inc. and a Director for Pershing LLC, a BNY Mellon company. In his role as Chief Operating Officer, Joel is directly responsible for the implementation and execution of investments decisions, operations, risk, regulatory, technology, relationship management and due diligence functions for Lockwood Advisors, Inc., (Lockwood) an SEC-registered investment adviser. Joel also serves as the central point of contact for senior management of Pershing Advisor Solutions and is responsible for the daily management of product, sales, service and operations for managed account solutions. He is a member of the Managed Investments Executive Committee and is Chair for the Lockwood Investment Committee.
During the past 17+ years, Joel has held various positions within the firm ranging from the manager of affiliate conversions, client development associate, training manager, institutional sales relationship manager and manager of enterprise sales for Pershing Managed Investments. Before joining Lockwood and Pershing in 1996, Joel was a retail broker in New York City, New York. He has more than 20 years of financial services experience.
Joel earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in Criminal Justice from Temple University. He has also completed the Securities Industry Institute® program, sponsored by Securities Industry and Financial Markets Association (SIFMA), at the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania.


Matthew Forester Chief Investment Officer and Director of Investments, Lockwood Advisors, Inc., a BNY Mellon company  
Matthew Forester is the Chief Investment Officer and Director of Investments for Lockwood Advisors, Inc. and a Director for Pershing, a BNY Mellon company. In his role, Matthew provides input into Lockwood's proprietary investment models and reviews all updates for Lockwood’s discretionary products. He is a member of the Lockwood Investment Committee.
Prior to joining Lockwood, Matthew was Chief Investment Officer of NewSquare Capital, LLC. He was responsible for the design and management of the firm’s proprietary portfolios. He also spent nearly 20 years at Cumberland Advisors, Inc. where he managed the firm’s U.S. Equity, International Equity, Emerging Markets Equity and global asset class ETF portfolios. He has more than 27 years of investment experience.
Matthew earned his Bachelor of Science in Economics from The Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania.


Tara McCarten Chief Administrative Officer Lockwood Advisors, Inc., a BNY Mellon Company Managing Director Pershing LLC, a BNY Mellon company
Tara Eirich McCarten is a Managing Director for Pershing LLC, a BNY Mellon Company. She is Chief Administrative Office (CAO) for the firm’s Managed Investments business, Lockwood Advisors, Inc. and for Pershing affiliate, Albridge Solutions. In addition to her CAO responsibilities, Tara leads Risk, Strategy and Corporate Governance for the three business lines. Tara joined Pershing in 2008 as director of Operations, overseeing New Accounts, Customer Service, Account Maintenance, Trading, Reconciliation and Performance Reporting for Managed Investments.
Previous to joining Pershing, Tara was executive director with Morgan Stanley, overseeing Fixed Income and Equity Customer Service for the Americas. Prior to joining Morgan Stanley, Tara was the chief operating officer for The MONY Group, where she headed up operational oversight, management and administration of MONY Securities' Broker Dealer.
Tara was awarded 2008 and 2013 Pershing Leadership Awards and the 2011 Super Achiever Award. She earned a Bachelor of Science Degree from St. Joseph’s University.







